-- Rajaratnam, Chiesi Ask for More Information on Charges, Separate Trials
-- Bob Van Voris
-- 2010-06-23T14:24:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-23/rajaratnam-chiesi-ask-for-more-information-on-charges-separate-trials.html

          
          
             Raj Rajaratnam and Danielle S.
Chiesi, co-defendants in the biggest hedge-fund insider-trading
case, asked a federal judge to allow them to be tried separately
and to order prosecutors to give them more information about the
charges they face.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Bob Van Voris in New York at 
 rvanvoris@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        